    "Here we assume the axiom of choice.foot_31 Lemma 6.5 (2-Saturated Elementary Extensions).",
    "For every full possibility frame F = ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I, P ⟩, viewed as a structure for the first-order language L 1 (I, P) with identity, binary predicate symbols ⊑ and Ṙi for each i ∈ I, and a unary predicate symbol Ẋ for each X ∈ P, there is a L 1 (I, P)structureF s = ⟨S s, ⊑ s, {R s i } i∈I, P s ⟩ such that: 1.",
    "F s is a 2-saturated L 1 (I, P)-elementary extension of F; 2.",
    "⟨S s, ⊑ s, {R s i } i∈I ⟩ is an L 1 (I)-elementary extension of ⟨S, ⊑, {R i } i∈I ⟩; 3.",
    "F ′ = ⟨S s, ⊑ s, {R s i } i∈I, RO(S s, ⊑ s)⟩ is a full possibility frame.Proof."
